  <h1>The Espanola Mill and the BMI Group</h1>
  <p class="lead">A major redevelopment in the territory, and the questions about how members fit in.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-compiled and unofficial.</strong> This is a member-compiled summary, not an official communication of Sagamok Anishnawbek or the BMI Group. <a href="/about#corrections">Tell us what we got wrong</a> and we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  <p>The former Domtar pulp and paper mill in Espanola closed in November 2023. In 2025 the BMI Group, an Ontario company that acquires and redevelops end-of-use paper mills, purchased the site, about 8,823 acres including several dams and a 16 megawatt hydroelectric plant, and renamed the project "Bioveld North," a bioeconomy and energy park. BMI is engaging Sagamok Anishnawbek and Whitefish River First Nation as Indigenous partners, and Sagamok's leadership appeared at the public launch.</p>

  <p>On May 12, 2026, in a closed session, Council approved a non-disclosure agreement with the BMI Group for the Espanola Mill "Pulp Plus" project and directed the Chief to sign (Motion 2026/05 #04). The minutes describe an existing Sagamok and BMI memorandum of understanding as the "foundation for future longer-term agreements." The terms, and what Sagamok is committing, are not public.</p>

  <p>This could be a significant opportunity in the treaty territory. The open questions are about process.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'Questions members can ask' } only %}
  <ul>
    <li>Were members told or consulted before the Nation signed onto this?</li>
    <li>What is Sagamok committing, in money, equity, or land?</li>
    <li>Why is the Nation signing a non-disclosure agreement, and what does that agreement keep from members?</li>
    <li>What is "Pulp Plus," is it a separate entity?</li>
  </ul>

  <p>See also <a href="/communities/sagamok/awaiting-council">questions awaiting an answer</a>, and the <a href="/standard">shared transparency standard</a>: a commitment made in the members' name should follow from members being informed, not come before it.</p>

